.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on setup dependencies**\\n\\nI need to finalize the deterministic setup for dependencies. For instance, org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1 is listed as a testImplementation, ensuring LogHelper works since it references LoggingAdapter/InternalApi. I should use a version that aligns with pekko-parsing 2.0.0-M1. \\n\\nThen there's org.scala-lang:scala-reflect:2.13.18, which is necessary for macro implementation. I'm considering whether to include scala-compiler since the POM doesn’t provide it. I recall that the normal Scala test scaffold might not include it either, but existing build configurations do use it for macro annotations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying macro annotations**\\n\\nI’ve realized that for the LogHelper definition macros, there’s no need for -Ymacro-annotations since the artifact in version 2.0.0-M1 doesn't include any annotation macros. It's good that I could simplify things here and avoid unnecessary complexity in the setup. Keeping things straightforward helps ensure everything works smoothly and as intended! I always want to make sure I'm on the right track with these dependencies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The 2.0.0-M1 artifact is a tiny internal Scala macro jar; meaningful coverage requires its provided dependencies on the test classpath and tests must target the remaining macro APIs rather than removed ccompat classes.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"pekko-parsing declares pekko-actor as a provided dependency, and its LogHelper API directly references org.apache.pekko.event.LoggingAdapter and org.apache.pekko.annotation.InternalApi.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.scala-lang:scala-reflect:2.13.18\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The artifact contains Scala 2 macro implementations using scala.reflect.macros.blackbox, and its POM declares scala-reflect 2.13.18 as provided.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use Scala tests placed in package org.apache.pekko or org.apache.pekko.macros so package-private private[pekko] APIs are accessible. For 2.0.0-M1, do not import or test org.apache.pekko.http.ccompat.pre213/since213 classes; they existed in 1.3.0 but are no longer present. Focus coverage on org.apache.pekko.macros.LogHelper and LogHelperMacro, for example with a small in-package LogHelper implementation that invokes debug/info/warning without requiring external services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact has only internal/private Pekko macro APIs in 2.0.0-M1, so generated tests that assume public parser APIs or old ccompat annotation classes will fail to compile.\",\n    \"Scala macro tests are sensitive to Scala version alignment; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0966c59e7c443cfa016a42f33278ec81979a8e0ae05d9da306\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3548, "output": 1471, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40347, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782772516119, "responseId": "resp_0966c59e7c443cfa016a42f3249bc88197b36e7c2d0e1b31d2"}}
